# Preservation: crates/kailash-\*/ stays intact

The `crates/kailash-pact/` crate provides D/T/R envelope primitives.
See `crates/kailash-core/src/runtime.rs` for the dispatch loop. The
`crates/kailash-ml/` crate is the binding into kailash-align.

Bare prose mentions like the kailash-rs repo or "this lives in
kailash-py" are also preserved — only path-anchored backticked
references get rewritten.

Public PyPI package names in dep specs stay intact:
"kailash-dataflow>=2.0.3", "kailash-pact", "kailash-ml".
